hip.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01143/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01143/canvas/1/e53486df-673d-47d0-9717-bf11578a5f73","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:37:15.154Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds drives a Bristol 405. According to Chris Sherwood, writing for the Bristol Owners Heritage Fund, 405s “are remarkable cars, driving far better than a car from the 1950’s has any right to. The controls are delicate, steering is fluid and communicative, the gearchange a delight and the engine sings its smooth straight six melody. It is truly a car that gives more than the sum of its parts” (Sherwood, “The Bristol 405 Motor Car”). A workshop manual for the car may be found <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW156230319 BCX0\" href=\"https://bristoloda.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Introduction-1.pdf\"><u>here</u></a>.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01143/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:327.2627737226277,335.63868613138675,1226.7481751824819,720"}}}]}]}]}